               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1357" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1357" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1357" type="surname" value="KERSEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1357" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT KERSEY</persName>
                  </hi>, Jun. The prisoner has been in my father's employ since last Whit Monday. I marked a crown, a half-crown, and one shilling—I placed them in the till with other silver, making 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. together about six o'clock in the evening of the 24th of November—and about half-past o'clock the policeman searched the prisoner in my presence—no money was found on him, but a crown and a half-crown piece were found under the chair where he was sitting, and a shilling behind the door—it was all marked money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1358" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1358" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1358" type="surname" value="KERSEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1358" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM KERSEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the witness's brother I was set to detect this youth—about half-past six o'clock I saw him reach over the counter, unlock the till, and draw it out—he took out some money—I could not see what it was, but it was large coin—I waited till my brother came out of the yard, and then I went for the policeman—when I came back the money was on the ground—the prisoner said he would not do it any more.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18361128-name-1359" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1359" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1359" type="surname" value="SOLE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18361128-name-1359" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE SOLE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable R</hi> 174.) I went and saw the the prisoner sitting in the chair—Mr. Kersey said he had dropped something—I looked under the chair, and found the crown-piece and the half-crown—I then found the shilling behind the door, near shutter that stood there—I found a sixpence, and some copper on the prisoner—in going along th</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183611280214"></xptr>
               <p>prisoner met his brother, and he asked what he had done, I said, "Robbed his master of 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">l</hi>."—he said, "No, it was only 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>."</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
